```cpp
#include <simplemc/mpi.hpp>
#include <fmt/core.h>

int main(int argc, char** argv) {
  // initialize MPI environment and communicator
  simplemc::mpi::environment env(argc, argv);
  simplemc::mpi::communicator comm;

  // print message on each process
  fmt::print("Hello world, from {} of {} processes.\n", comm.rank(), comm.size());
}
```

**simplemc** is a library written in C++ that provides various tools to simplify the implementation of
Monte Carlo (MC) simulations with special focus on applications in computational physics.
Its functionality is similar to other already established codes like [ALPSCore](https://alpscore.org/)
or the MC part of [TRIQS](https://triqs.github.io/triqs/latest/).

The main purpose of this library is to help the user with common tasks that are encountered in nearly
all MC implementations. These tasks include, but are not limited to:
* accumulation of data,
* statistical analysis of results and error propagation,
* parallelization using MPI,
* saving and loading the simulation state in order to resume a simulation (serialization),
* parsing user input and configuration files,
* and more.

These tasks can take a considerable amount of effort and time to be implemented correctly and
efficiently.
Since they are rather mundane and not related to the actual (physics) problem, developers and
especially researchers often tend to neglect them, which can lead to subtle errors and bad user
experience.

**simplemc** aims to make it easier for both, developers and users.

@section contributors Contributors

This project has been in development for some years now and it has been refactored from the ground up 
a couple of times.

Contributions from other developers might have been lost in the process. Let me mention all the
people who contributed to the project along the way:

